It could be a new record.

31:52.600 --> 31:53.400
Is that right?

31:58.800 --> 32:00.280
Dad, there's cops.

32:00.400 --> 32:03.000
[music playing]

32:10.240 --> 32:11.120
Gidday, Ted.

32:15.720 --> 32:18.560
TED: Righto.

32:18.680 --> 32:20.080
[WHISPERS] What the bloody hell?

32:20.200 --> 32:23.560
[music playing]

32:34.120 --> 32:35.000
[chuckles]

32:43.680 --> 32:45.880
Stop looking.

32:46.000 --> 32:46.760
[chuckles]

32:48.760 --> 32:50.320
It's wacky Becky.

32:50.440 --> 32:51.440
Those leek munchers, eh?

32:51.560 --> 32:52.320
Whoa.

32:57.520 --> 32:58.840
How could you do this?

32:58.960 --> 33:01.720
How could you?

33:01.840 --> 33:03.440
What's he bloody on about?

33:03.560 --> 33:04.880
You hardly even know the bugger.What?

33:05.000 --> 33:06.360
Does he think you
called the cops on him?

33:06.480 --> 33:07.240
No way.

33:07.360 --> 33:09.680
Wests never dob.

33:09.800 --> 33:11.000
They certainly don't.

33:11.120 --> 33:12.360
[chuckles]

33:12.480 --> 33:13.520
That's right, officer--

33:13.640 --> 33:14.960
drugs.

33:15.080 --> 33:17.200
I've seen them.

33:17.320 --> 33:20.000
Well, here we are--

33:20.120 --> 33:21.360
just me and my two best boys.

33:24.320 --> 33:25.680
Things are looking
up, all right.

33:32.640 --> 33:34.720
You know what I'm
after, so hand it over.

33:41.160 --> 33:44.480
It's not even
real gold, you know.

33:44.600 --> 33:45.480
Doh!

33:45.600 --> 33:46.360
Ah!

33:59.520 --> 34:01.000
Ted, what is going on?

34:01.120 --> 34:02.200
Out you get, Mrs. West.

34:13.760 --> 34:15.160
Where are we?

34:15.280 --> 34:18.240
Why don't you look inthat letter box over there.

34:18.360 --> 34:19.680
You know I don't
like surprises,

34:19.800 --> 34:21.880
Oh, go on, you silly bint.

34:22.000 --> 34:22.760
[sighs]

34:33.560 --> 34:35.520
Ted?

34:35.640 --> 34:37.640
Are you going to
put that back on?

34:37.760 --> 34:39.880
Well, unless you've
had a better offer.

34:40.000 --> 34:41.080
What's this?

34:41.200 --> 34:44.200
That is the key to a castle--

34:44.320 --> 34:45.800
a castle for my queen.

34:45.920 --> 34:46.920
[music playing]

34:47.040 --> 34:50.000
Step aside, give
her room to move.

34:50.120 --> 34:52.360
Get yourself up.

34:52.480 --> 34:53.640
Oh, my God.

34:53.760 --> 34:54.520
Ted!

34:56.440 --> 34:57.240
What?

34:57.360 --> 34:58.680
Do you like it?

34:58.800 --> 35:00.200
You'd better because I puta bloody deposit on it.

35:00.320 --> 35:02.360
I fucking love it!

35:02.480 --> 35:04.840
[rock music playing]

35:04.960 --> 35:06.080
And I love you.

35:10.600 --> 35:13.520
You know, there's a littlesomething I want in return.

35:13.640 --> 35:17.560
You can roger me
any way you want.

35:17.680 --> 35:18.760
[laughter]

35:18.880 --> 35:20.560
Actually, I had
something else in mind--

35:20.680 --> 35:22.160
a bit of a party.

35:22.280 --> 35:25.160
[music playing]

35:42.800 --> 35:43.840
So this is their new place.

35:43.960 --> 35:45.640
Apparently.

35:45.760 --> 35:48.120
I thought they were on
the bones of their ass.

35:48.240 --> 35:51.320
So did I.

35:51.440 --> 35:52.560
Did he say what
this is all about?

35:52.680 --> 35:54.280
No.

35:54.400 --> 35:57.040
This is tremendous, Rita.

35:57.160 --> 35:59.400
We like it.

35:59.520 --> 36:02.360
Do have a drink.

36:02.480 --> 36:03.840
Ted.

36:03.960 --> 36:05.080
Mate.

36:05.200 --> 36:06.880
Good to see you.

36:07.000 --> 36:09.040
How's about we crack the
top off one of those?

36:09.160 --> 36:10.320
Sounds good.

36:10.440 --> 36:12.360
You can show the
ladies about hacienda.

36:12.480 --> 36:14.880
Love to.

36:15.000 --> 36:17.720
[cheering]

36:17.840 --> 36:19.640
You could play a good gameof backyard cricket out here.

36:19.760 --> 36:21.000
Any time.

36:21.120 --> 36:24.200
But first, a little business.

36:27.400 --> 36:29.160
What's this?

36:29.280 --> 36:32.880
Well, fair is fair,
and there's the share.

36:33.000 --> 36:34.840
Of what?

36:34.960 --> 36:37.200
Where'd you get this?

36:37.320 --> 36:39.000
I melted down all
those krugerrands.

36:39.120 --> 36:39.920
What do you think?

36:42.960 --> 36:44.280
[chuckles]

36:46.360 --> 36:47.920
Come on.

36:48.040 --> 36:49.760
It was a golden opportunity--

36:49.880 --> 36:54.400
a tavern full of punters, alleyes on the goggle box, Friday

36:54.520 --> 36:58.440
night's take still
sitting in the safe.

36:58.560 --> 36:59.880
You knocked off the tavern.

37:00.000 --> 37:01.400
You were in the bog.

37:01.520 --> 37:02.720
Nope.

37:02.840 --> 37:04.800
But I thought you were
out, going it alone.

37:04.920 --> 37:07.200
I've reconsidered.

37:07.320 --> 37:08.520
Nah, it's your job.

37:08.640 --> 37:09.400
You keep it.

37:09.520 --> 37:10.760
What's mine is yours.

37:10.880 --> 37:12.960
Piss off.

37:13.080 --> 37:14.800
Hey, we go way back.

37:14.920 --> 37:17.360
I'm not some bugger runningon his own in his singlet.

37:17.480 --> 37:20.240
I need a team.

37:20.360 --> 37:26.080
We get back in business, andMike McCarthy can suck on that.

37:26.200 --> 37:26.960
What do you say?

37:30.280 --> 37:32.320
All those bedrooms!

37:32.440 --> 37:33.640
Just for the three of you.

37:33.760 --> 37:36.480
Oh, I've always
wanted a breakfast bar.

37:36.600 --> 37:39.120
Tina, can you a loveand take Carol's asparagus

37:39.240 --> 37:40.240
rolls out to the men.

37:40.360 --> 37:41.560
They're a wee bit soggy.

37:41.680 --> 37:42.640
I'm sure they're perfect.

37:46.080 --> 37:50.240
Did you want to have alittle girl talk, Ngaire?

37:50.360 --> 37:52.520
How did you get this place?

37:52.640 --> 37:53.960
My husband's a good provider.

37:54.080 --> 37:55.800
Bullshit.

37:55.920 --> 37:57.400
You cashed in the
krugerrands, didn't you?

37:57.520 --> 37:58.640
I thought we
weren't meant to touch

37:58.760 --> 38:00.240
them until we were on our own.

38:00.360 --> 38:03.200
I didn't touch them, Carol--

38:03.320 --> 38:04.880
even though you wanted me to.

38:05.000 --> 38:06.400
Excuse me?

38:06.520 --> 38:10.000
You cut me off, so I'd getdesperate and break cover,

38:10.120 --> 38:13.920
and then you could blame mewhen it was all your idea.

38:14.040 --> 38:18.320
I caught him right herein our bed with that slapper

38:18.440 --> 38:21.000
from Swanson!

38:21.120 --> 38:24.440
He should pay for
this-- bloody pay!

38:24.560 --> 38:26.120
I was a little bit upset.

38:26.240 --> 38:28.960
You were the one who said thatwe needed insurance for a time

38:29.080 --> 38:30.280
when our men weren't around.

38:30.400 --> 38:31.880
You both saw
the sense in that.

38:32.000 --> 38:33.360
Yeah, we did.

38:33.480 --> 38:34.560
Yeah, it's Christmas eve.

38:34.680 --> 38:37.200
This town's deader
than a door nail.

38:37.320 --> 38:41.240
[chuckles]

38:41.360 --> 38:42.160
[whistles]

38:42.280 --> 38:45.120
[music playing]

38:56.680 --> 38:58.560
Calling the police was
never part of the plan.

38:58.680 --> 39:03.480
I told you back then, I haveno idea who called the police.

39:03.600 --> 39:07.320
I assumed it was you to get backat Lefty for screwing around.

39:07.440 --> 39:09.960
You mean, it
wasn't just bad luck?

39:10.080 --> 39:12.520
It might have been so Ritacould get Ted out of the way

39:12.640 --> 39:14.680
while she went up north
for a little while.

39:14.800 --> 39:16.600
That time you went on holiday.

39:16.720 --> 39:20.640
When you came back, Wolftold Desiree that while you

39:20.760 --> 39:23.800
were away Mommy got fat.

39:23.920 --> 39:26.200
Eating was my only comfort.

39:26.320 --> 39:28.520
My husband was
doing three years.

39:28.640 --> 39:30.080
So was it a boy or a girl?

39:30.200 --> 39:32.960
I know you don't
like me, Ngaire,

39:33.080 --> 39:35.240
but there was no
baby, all right?

39:35.360 --> 39:37.560
And this kind of bullshitis just dangerous

39:37.680 --> 39:41.160
gossip, because if we
turn on each other, then

39:41.280 --> 39:44.120
we're all sunk.

39:44.240 --> 39:47.560
Have you still got
your insurance?

39:47.680 --> 39:48.600
Yes.

39:48.720 --> 39:50.080
Hidden away.

39:50.200 --> 39:52.040
How about you?

39:52.160 --> 39:55.040
[music playing]

